ps4: register reboot_notifier → ICC shutdown_final so console actually powers down

v72c (supersedes v72b approach which hooked pm_power_off and failed
silently in hardware testing).

Without this patch, `systemctl poweroff` halts Linux but the PS4
stays at standby (white LED on, fans on) until the EMC watchdog
times out ~30 s later and cuts power ungracefully.

v72b attempt (failed)
---------------------
The first iteration hooked Linux's pm_power_off callback. That fires
at the very end of kernel_power_off(), AFTER kernel_shutdown_prepare
has invoked every device's .shutdown callback — including bpcie/apcie
tearing down the ICC mailbox we need to talk through. On hardware
test (UART log checkpoint/uart-logs/2026-05-11_1532-v72b-poweroff-retry.log)
our handler was installed correctly at t=25.28s, but at shutdown
time the standard sequence

    [132.077] systemd-shutdown[1]: Powering off.
    [132.454] ACPI: PM: Preparing to enter system sleep state S5  (pm_power_off_prepare)
    [132.460] kvm: exiting hardware virtualization                (syscore_shutdown)
    [132.465] reboot: Power down                                  (pr_emerg, last log)

ran past the .shutdown callbacks. Our handler then either failed
silently (driver gone) or succeeded into a void (mailbox unmapped),
with UART also torn down so no error was visible. Console stayed at
standby — same behavior as no hook at all.

v72c fix
--------
Switch to register_reboot_notifier(), gated on action==SYS_POWER_OFF.
The reboot notifier list fires *before* device shutdown — early in
__do_sys_reboot() right after the syscall validates its magic
numbers. At that point bpcie/apcie ICC are still fully functional,
the ICC command reaches the EMC, and the EMC drops the console rails
mid-mdelay(3000).

We filter on SYS_POWER_OFF specifically so SYS_HALT and SYS_RESTART
go through unmodified — for restart Linux's reboot path runs, for
halt the system stays at standby intentionally.

Sony reference (RE'd from orbis-12.02.elf)
------------------------------------------
icc_power_shutdown_final (FUN_c8574860 in orbis-12.02.elf) builds an
ICC mailbox command:

    buf[1]      = 0x04   major = power
    buf[2..3]   = 0x0004 minor = shutdown_final
    buf[6..7]   = 0x0020 payload length = 32 bytes
    buf[8..]    = zeros

and sends it via icc_send_recv (FUN_c87e3050, from
freebsd/sys/dev/scesb/icc/icc.c). Our apcie_icc_cmd has the matching
signature; it auto-routes to bpcie_icc_cmd when bpcie_initialized, so
one call covers both Aeolia/Belize (PS4 phat/slim) and Baikal (PS4
CUH-15xx+).

The patch sends only the ICC mailbox command. If hardware test
shows the EMC needs the low-level MMIO sequence after the command
(Sony's icc_lowlevel_power_off, FUN_c85b2660 — writes to
icc_bar +0x1C8400..+0x1C8468), the follow-up adds that. Sketched
in the research note at
checkpoint/docs/research/orbis-kernel/2026-05-11-orbis-poweroff-discovered.md.

Files
-----
- New drivers/ps4/ps4-power.c (~120 LOC). Registers the notifier in a
  late_initcall so apcie/bpcie probes have completed.
- drivers/ps4/Makefile: one-line `obj-y += ps4-power.o` addition.
- patches/6.x-baikal/series: 0015 entry with rationale comment.

